.TH "zynqmp_pm_request_node" 9 "zynqmp_pm_request_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zynqmp_pm_request_node \- Request a node with specific capabilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" zynqmp_pm_request_node
.BI "(const u32 node "  ","
.BI "const u32 capabilities "  ","
.BI "const u32 qos "  ","
.BI "const enum zynqmp_pm_request_ack ack "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "node" 12
Node ID of the slave
.IP "capabilities" 12
Requested capabilities of the slave
.IP "qos" 12
Quality of service (not supported)
.IP "ack" 12
Flag to specify whether acknowledge is requested
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used by master to request particular node from firmware.
Every master must request node before using it.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns status, either success or error+reason
